    "## 4. Euler's method\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

    "# Specify step size and simulation length\n",
    "dx = [2.0,1.0,0.5,0.01]\n",
    "total_x = 20\n",
    "# Initial condition\n",
    "y0 = 1.0\n",
    "# Define k\n",
    "k = 1.2\n",
    "y0 = 1.0\n",
    "fig1 = plt.figure()\n",
    "rcn = 221\n",
    "for num in range(4):\n",
    "    N = int(total_x/dx[num])\n",
    "    x = np.linspace(0,total_x,N+1) # Store end point \n",

    "    y[0] = y0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        y[i+1] = y[i]+dx[num]*(-k*y[i])\n",

    "    rcn +=1"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "### Question 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   "source": [
    "# Specify step size and simulation length\n",
    "dxp = 0.1\n",
    "total_x = 20\n",
    "Np = int(total_x/dxp)\n",
    "xp = np.linspace(0,total_x,Np+1) # Store end point \n",
    "yp = np.zeros(Np+1)\n",
    "yp[0] = -1\n",
    "for i in range(Np):\n",
    "    yp[i+1] = yp[i] + dxp*(xp[i]*yp[i]*yp[i])\n",
    "plt.plot(xp,yp,label='Approx, dx = 0.1')\n",
    "plt.plot(xp,-2/(2+xp*xp),label='Exact')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('x')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('y')\n",
    "plt.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Once $\\Delta x > 1$, the solution is completely unstable.  The analytic solution is $y = -2/(2+x^2)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def euler_solver(fun,y0,dt,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Solve dy/dt = fun(y,t) using Euler's method.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun  f(y,t)\n",
    "    y0   Initial condition\n",
    "    dt   Step size\n",
    "    N    Number of steps\n",
    "    Returns: array of length N+1 with values of y\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    retval = np.zeros((N+1,len(y0)))\n",
    "    retval[0] = y0\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        t += dt\n",
    "        retval[i+1] = retval[i] + dt*fun(t,retval[i])\n",
    "    return retval"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RHS_SHO(t,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return acceleration of SHO, defines k & m internally\n",
    "    Now includes damping term, coefficient c defined externally\"\"\"\n",
    "    k = 1.0\n",
    "    m = 1.0\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -k*x/m -c*v/m\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},

    "# Specify damping terms\n",
    "carr = [0.0,1.0,2.0,5.0]\n",
    "dt = 0.01\n",
    "fig1 = plt.figure()\n",
    "rcn = 221\n",
    "for num in range(4):\n",
    "    c = carr[num]\n",
    "    motion = euler_solver(RHS_SHO,[1.0,0.0],0.01,1000)\n",
    "    t = np.arange(0,10.01,0.01)\n",
    "    ax1 = fig1.add_subplot(rcn)\n",
    "    ax1.plot(t,motion[:,0])\n",

   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "### Question 4\n",
    "\n",
    "This simply adds a driving term, $A \\cos(\\omega t)$ to the right hand side.  The relationship between the different constants is interesting, and worth playing with."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RHS_SHO_Driven(t,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return acceleration of SHO, defines k & m internally\n",
    "    Now includes damping term, coefficient c defined externally\n",
    "    and driving term\"\"\"\n",
    "    k = 1.0\n",
    "    m = 1.0\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -k*x/m -c*v/m + 3*np.cos(t) # Explicitly set omega = 10\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## 5. Beyond Euler\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1\n",
    "\n",
    "We need to reproduce RK4 from the in-class notebook:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RK4_solver(fun,y0,dt,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Solve dy/dt = fun(y,t) using fourth-order RK method.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun  f(y,t)\n",
    "    y0   Initial condition - assumed to be two-component\n",
    "    dt   Step size\n",
    "    N    Number of steps\n",
    "    Returns: two arrays of length N+1 (x and v or equivalent)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    x = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    v = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    x[0] = y0[0]\n",
    "    v[0] = y0[1]\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    y = y0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        k1 = dt*fun(y,t)\n",
    "        k2 = dt*fun(y+0.5*k1,t+0.5*dt)\n",
    "        k3 = dt*fun(y+0.5*k2,t+0.5*dt)\n",
    "        k4 = dt*fun(y+k3,t+dt)\n",
    "        y=y+(k1+2*k2+2*k3+k4)/6\n",
    "        x[i+1] = y[0]\n",
    "        v[i+1] = y[1]\n",
    "    return x, v"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def pred_corr_solver(fun,y0,dt,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Solve dy/dt = fun(y,t) using predictor-corrector method.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun  f(y,t)\n",
    "    y0   Initial condition - assumed to be two-component\n",
    "    dt   Step size\n",
    "    N    Number of steps\n",
    "    Returns: two arrays of length N+1 (x and v or equivalent)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    x = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    v = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    x[0] = y0[0]\n",
    "    v[0] = y0[1]\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    y = y0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        k1 = fun(y,t)\n",
    "        ypred = y + dt*k1\n",
    "        k2 = fun(ypred,t+dt)\n",
    "        y = y + 0.5*dt*(k1 + k2)\n",
    "        x[i+1] = y[0]\n",
    "        v[i+1] = y[1]\n",
    "    return x, v"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RHS_nonlinear_pendulum(y,t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implements linear pendulum RHS for ODE solver\"\"\"\n",
    "    g = 9.8\n",
    "    L = 1.0\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -g*np.sin(x)/L\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]

  {

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Boundary value problems\n",
    "\n",
    "### Questions 1 & 2\n",
    "\n",
    "We must redefine our equations.  The simplest model would involve no force in $x$ and gravity in $y$ (question 1), but it might be more interesting to add in a damping (air-resistance) term $\\mathbf{F}_{damp} = -c d\\mathbf{v}/dt$.  We will leave `c` to be defined outside the function to allow both possibilities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def ball_vertical_RHS(yin,t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate RHS for projectile ODE\"\"\"\n",
    "    x = yin[0]\n",
    "    z = yin[1]\n",
    "    vx = yin[2]\n",
    "    vz = yin[3]\n",
    "    dx = vx\n",
    "    dz = vz\n",
    "    dvx = -c*vx\n",
    "    dvz = -g - c*vz\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dz,dvx,dvz])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RK4_solver_2d(fun,y0,dt,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Solve dy/dt = fun(y,t) using fourth-order RK method.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun  f(y,t)\n",
    "    y0   Initial condition - assumed to be four-component\n",
    "    dt   Step size\n",
    "    N    Number of steps\n",
    "    Returns: two arrays of length N+1 (x and v or equivalent)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    x = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    z = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    vx = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    vz = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    x[0] = y0[0]\n",
    "    z[0] = y0[1]\n",
    "    vx[0] = y0[2]\n",
    "    vz[0] = y0[3]\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    y = y0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        k1 = dt*fun(y,t)\n",
    "        k2 = dt*fun(y+0.5*k1,t+0.5*dt)\n",
    "        k3 = dt*fun(y+0.5*k2,t+0.5*dt)\n",
    "        k4 = dt*fun(y+k3,t+dt)\n",
    "        y=y+(k1+2*k2+2*k3+k4)/6\n",
    "        x[i+1] = y[0]\n",
    "        z[i+1] = y[1]\n",
    "        vx[i+1] = y[2]\n",
    "        vz[i+1] = y[3]\n",
    "    return x, z, vx, vz"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initial velocity required is  88.29445393773669\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "g  = 9.81 # m/s^2\n",
    "t0 = 0.0  # s\n",
    "t1 = 10.0 # s\n",
    "dt = 0.05 # s\n",
    "N  = int((t1-t0)/dt)\n",
    "c = 1.0   # Strong damping\n",
    "v_guess_x = 10   # m/s\n",
    "v_guess_1z = 0   # m/s\n",
    "v_guess_2z = 200 # m/s\n",
    "\n",
    "h1x, h1z, vtmpx, vtmpz = RK4_solver_2d(ball_vertical_RHS,[0.0,0.0,v_guess_x,v_guess_1z],dt,N)\n",
    "h2x, h2z, vtmpx, vtmpz = RK4_solver_2d(ball_vertical_RHS,[0.0,0.0,v_guess_x,v_guess_2z],dt,N)\n",
    "tol = 1e-4\n",
    "err = h2z[N] - h1z[N]\n",
    "while err > tol:\n",
    "    v_new = v_guess_2z - h2z[N]*(v_guess_2z - v_guess_1z)/(h2z[N] - h1z[N])\n",
    "    err = abs(v_guess_1z - v_guess_2z)\n",
    "    v_guess_1z = v_guess_2z\n",
    "    v_guess_2z = v_new\n",

    "def RHS_nonlinear_damped_pendulum_param(y,t,g,L,c):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implements linear pendulum RHS for ODE solver\"\"\"\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -g*np.sin(x)/L-c*v\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy import integrate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g  = 9.81 # m/s^2\n",
    "L  = 1.0  # m\n",
    "c  = 1.0  # /s\n",
    "t0 = 0.0  # s\n",
    "t1 = 10.0 # s\n",
    "dt = 0.05 # s\n",
    "N  = int((t1-t0)/dt)\n",
    "t = np.arange(t0,t1+0.5*dt,dt)\n",
    "ode_solve = integrate.odeint(RHS_nonlinear_damped_pendulum_param,np.array([0.1*np.pi,0.0]),t,args=(g,L,c))"
   ]
  },
